javax.management

Class BadAttributeValueExpException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • javax.management.BadAttributeValueExpException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class BadAttributeValueExpException
extends Exception
    Thrown when an invalid MBean attribute is passed to a query constructing method. This exception is used internally by JMX during the evaluation of a query. User code does not usually see it.
    Since:
    1.5
    See Also:
